| Setting         | Description                         | Example                                 |
| --------------- | ----------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| AimbotEnabled | Turns the aimbot on or off          | true / false                       |
| AimPart       | The part of the enemy to aim at     | "Head" / "HumanoidRootPart"         |
| Sensitivity   | How fast the aimbot moves to target | 1 = instant snap, 0.1 = very smooth |
| TeamCheck    | Ignore teammates if true          | true / false                        |

| Setting           | Description                     | Example                  |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| ESPEnabled      | Turns ESP boxes on/off          | true / false         |
| ESPColorName    | Color of the ESP box            | "green" / "#00FF00"  |
| ESPFilled       | Should the box be filled        | true / false         |
| ESPThickness    | Thickness of the box outline    | 1 (thin) → 5 (thick) |
| ESPTransparency | Transparency of the box         | 0.1 → 1              |
| ESPRainbow      | Rainbow mode for dynamic colors | true / false         |

| Setting           | Description                    | Example                              |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| FOVEnabled      | Show or hide the FOV circle    | true / false                     |
| FOVColorName    | Color of the circle            | "white" / "#FFFFFF"              |
| FOVRadius       | Radius in pixels               | 60 → 200                         |
| FOVFilled       | Should the circle be filled    | true / false                     |
| FOVTransparency | Circle transparency            | 0.1 → 1                          |
| FOVThickness    | Thickness of the circle line   | 1 → 5                            |
| FOVRainbow      | Rainbow mode for dynamic color | true / false                     |
| FOVCircleSides  | How many sides the circle has  | 32 → 128 (more sides = smoother) |


